caption: Michelle is amazing!
Great atmosphere. Good drinks.
Great roof top atmosphere, even during COVID.
The rooftop is pretty cool. Their place is a little small but they make up for it with great atmosphere and staff. Very healthy with the COVID requirements.
A good place! Nice, unpretentious interior, good service, delicious food!

Great spot! We hosted my friend's birthday here and they provided us with the downstairs bar space for no reservation fee or drink minimum! All the party guests raved at how great the spot was and all the employees were champs for helping us out. Definitely will come back when it's warmer to check out the fun rooftop
LOVED EVERYTHING!!!! My friend and I went here on a Saturday night because we were bar hopping, and we ended up staying for 3-4 hours. Great vibes from the staff!!! The drinks were awesome too!!

A nice hidden gem within a busy area. Came here on a friday night with some coworkers expecting the bar to be crowded. When we went there wasn't too many people and we basically had the roof to ourselves. The drink selection was great and the margaritas I had were of good quality. The only thing holding back this place is the food selection which only consisted of empanadas.
Very friendly,very organized,very nice spot for activities

Was there with my friends last night for New Years and had a terrible experience with the manager. He was super disrespectful to one of my friends just because we were waiting for an Uber in the hallway.

We went for New Years. Music was ok as well as the open bar. However, the manager treated us horrible! He should literally been fired! Cant understand how a place runs with a manager as irrespecful as him
New bar with cute decor. On offer: empanadas, margheritas, and other drinks.
(Translated by Google) Armando Martinez cuts  (Original) Armando cortes martinez

Sorry, editing my response, so that the owner knows I read and acknowledge that they are trying. I used to come here when it was 1903, my visit here after the change from 1903 to Cortez was quite some time ago. I'd have to visit again to give a better response. I do remember waiting at a table for 45 mins without being addressed.

This place was nice. The deck is on the roof which is a few steps up but there are signs indicating where to go. The drinks were pretty good and service prompt. I went later in the evening and had an awesome view of the bustling neighborhood. I'm giving it 5 stars based on my experience but may update after visiting during the day.
Cute rooftop bar with decent happy hour specials

Drinks are good but food needs a lot of work. Only options on roof are empanadas or chips and salsa. Chips were from a grocery store bag and salsa was definitely Pace from a jar. I could do this on my apartment roof.

It was great for a hot second when it opened. Then they removed all the food, which is super lame. The tacos were so good and now all you get is a rooftop always reserved by groups. No more tacos is an abomination
Hosted my birthday Happy Hour here. It is a hidden gem. Amazing rooftop and great vibes. The drinks are amazing!
Hidden rooftop. Get the cocktail pitchers - worth the excursion. Staff is great
Overpriced, but we all enjoyed ourselves! The rooftop was great! Yes, small area, but enjoyable!
This is a really nice place. Wish they had a better menu.
Drinks were a little weak in my opinion. Came for the rooftop bar but the part of the bar overlooking the city was occupied by two reserved groups already 😕. Will have to come back another time!

This is one of my favorite U Street bars. Everyone goes down the street to El Rey but Cortez is the real hidden gem. Prices are reasonable, it's always full of people but never feels crowded, and it has a great rooftop! I love ending the night here with margaritas on the roof.
I liked it
Cramped atmosphere and inefficient bartender upstairs. Didnt enjoy my time here.
Pretty crowded and no control of the stairwells. Good place other than that though! Great staff.
It was ok
The tacos are really good, and with the trip! Not big on space, but the service was good and the staff were very friendly.
Awesome Happy Hour! Really nice service, and a cool rooftop spot.

The decor was nice and it was clean.  The tacos taste great and the price was right.  However... there was a hostess that never moved from behind the bar to do anything for our table and it was just us and her in there!! She stayed on her phone the entire night even when we were standing there.  The kitchen staff that brought the tacos were far more friendly and helpful.  The place was empty and I'm pretty sure that's why.
Went for HH, taco/beer special is awesome. Margaritas are 7/10. Nice ambiance, I have to check it out during the summer.

The salsa has a very dry and smokey flavor. Chips are too thick and hard. The tacos were excessively bland, with extremely hot peppers on it. $5 for one taco isn’t a competitive price compared to El Rey’s around the corner.  Drinks were good. Price for a pitcher was again too high compared to nearby competitors.
Super cool place, good happy hour. The artwork is phenomenal.
$5 tacos, cauliflower one was the best, cool vibes and good music, awesome happy hour specials
Service was amazing and the margaritas are the best I have had outside of Mexico!

I hosted an event at Cortez and it was amazing! The venue was nice (we booked the heated rooftop and it had great views of U street) and it was perfect for the group size I had (about 30). The drinks were really good (our favorite was the cranberry ginger marg) and the bartender was great. Excellent service and venue! Also, I wasn’t even expecting this but the music was fun too.
This place should get way more traffic than it does. Incredible food, great vibe, lovely staff. I am there at least once a week - highly recommend the tacos on Sunday or during HH.

Came here and got their elote and also got their cauliflower taco. I didn’t really like their cauliflower taco. It just tasted weird to be. Nothing wrong with it but cauliflowers shouldn’t be in tacos in my opinion. That was the only vegetarian option available. The elote was absolutely delicious. Perfect amount of sauce and cheese.

I went to Cortez DC for a celebration in the semiprivate area on the rooftop. It had a small rooftop area but it's great for happy hour. The fish tacos that I had wasn't bad and the frozen margarita was your standard margarita.

The taco and beer happy hour deal is definitely a steal! Each taco we had was exceptionally stuffed, and the flavor profiles of each were amazing. The fish taco in particular had an amazing sauce that I'll definitely go back for.
Happy hour is cheap and worth it

My friend and I were at Cortez on Wednesday night. We had a great time on the rooftop bar. All of the food was delicious, especially the fish tacos and elote. Food and drinks were at a great price and very affordable and the bar is filled with cool decor that catches your eye.

Really awesome bar! Spent hours on the rooftop of this place. The decor is quite fun. Really enjoyed the fish tacos and the deal that comes with two beers, chips, guac, and salsa! Really personable bartenders. Worth a visit especially on a nice day.
Had a great time last night! Ken was so great and even found me a phone charger so I could get an Uber home. If I was local this would totally be my spot.
Went with the ladies for a HH.  The rooftop is fantastic, and enjoyed the tacos with free beer for a great mid-week special.  I really loved the steak and chicken tinga tacos.
I never ate here but I love the roof top! It's a great spot if you want to grab a drink on a small and quiet roof in DC
The margaritas had no alcohol in them and were overpriced. Wait staff was great. Guacamole was average. Nice rooftop.
Good tacos and nice vibe!
I little pricey for the vibe

This place has potential - regardless of reviews, you should definitely check it out. The location and venue itself is really nice and the rooftop is definitely a new hot spot I'll likely stop by often. The tacos were pretty good, but can't say they're worth the price. Margaritas were pretty good as well, but nothing to write home about. They just opened up recently though, so I'm excited to see how they use the constructive criticism to their benefit. Staff was very kind and open to feedback.
Great rooftop view, frozen margs, and right off U!!
Tacos are spicey! And the service is great. Stopped by for an afternoon snack and a drink on the rooftop.
Go for the drinks. Beware of the food. Lively atmosphere.

The cost of the tacos simply don't add up given the quality of the ingredients and service. I suggest walking two more blocks up to El Rey where the tacos are better, the full service is quicker, and it won't break your bank.

Honestly $5 for a single taco, even in that neighborhood is obnoxious. The tacos themselves were mediocre, with far too much lettuce/cabbage.  $7 for a can of beer, $12 for a tiny gauc. The quality of the ingredients does not match the prices or the neighborhood. Better options in the area.
Really enjoy the fun atmosphere and vibe at Cortez DC - Wonderful mixed drinks and beautiful rooftop restaurant. A must see in DC

Pretty good spot. The rooftop was amazing at sunset. The fish and cauliflower tacos were solid and had a kick, but probably not worth $5. They had a really cool dining set up where we were easily able to bring a bunch of tables together for our group of 12. I will be coming back!
Amazing food, tequila bar and service!
